$ System.Management.Automation.PSCredential (class)

The `System.Management.Automation.PSCredential` class centralizes the management of usernames, → development/security/password[passwords] and
→ development/security/credential[credentials].

An instance of `PSCredential` is returned by the → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/credential/get[`get-credential` cmdlet].

The two important properties of a `PSCredential` object are `UserName` (which is a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/String[`System.String`]) and
`Password` (which is a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Security/SecureString[`System.Security.SecureString`]).

sa:

    Creating a `PSCredential` object → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/credential/get#get-credential-no-interaction[without user interaction] 

  → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/host/ui#host-ui-PromptForCredential[`$host.ui.promptForCredential(…)`] 
